# Privacy Policy

**Last updated:** 20-09-2025

This privacy notice for **Spottr** (“we,” “us,” or “our”) describes how and why we might collect, store, use, and/or share (“process”) your information when you use our services (“Services”), such as when you:

- Download and use our mobile application (Spottr), or any other application of ours that links to this privacy notice
- Engage with us in other related ways, including any sales, marketing, or events

**Questions or concerns?** Reading this privacy notice will help you understand your privacy rights and choices. If you do not agree with our policies and practices, please do not use our Services.

---

## 1. WHAT INFORMATION DO WE COLLECT?

We collect personal information that you voluntarily provide to us when you register on the Services, express an interest in obtaining information about us or our products and Services, when you participate in activities on the Services, or otherwise when you contact us.

The personal information we collect may include the following:

- Name
- Email address
- Date of birth
- Gender
- Location
- Profile photos
- Personality quiz answers
- Messages sent through the app
- Gym membership preferences

---

## 2. HOW DO WE PROCESS YOUR INFORMATION?

We process your information to:

- Deliver and facilitate delivery of services to users
- Enable user-to-user communications
- Evaluate and improve our services, products, marketing, and user experience
- Identify usage trends
- Protect our services
- Request feedback
- Respond to user inquiries or offer support
- Send administrative information

---

## 3. WHEN AND WITH WHOM DO WE SHARE YOUR PERSONAL INFORMATION?

We may share your information in specific situations and with the following categories of third parties:

- Firebase (Google) for authentication, database, and analytics
- Cloud service providers to store and manage your content (e.g., images, messages)
- Law enforcement or other authorities if required by applicable law

---

## 4. DO WE USE COOKIES AND OTHER TRACKING TECHNOLOGIES?

We may use cookies and similar tracking technologies (like Firebase Analytics) to access or store information.

---

## 5. HOW LONG DO WE KEEP YOUR INFORMATION?

We keep your information for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this privacy notice unless otherwise required by law.

---

## 6. HOW DO WE KEEP YOUR INFORMATION SAFE?

We implement appropriate technical and organizational security measures designed to protect your personal information. However, no electronic transmission or storage is 100% secure.

---

## 7. DO WE COLLECT INFORMATION FROM MINORS?

**No.** We do not knowingly collect data from or market to children under 18 years of age.

---

## 8. WHAT ARE YOUR PRIVACY RIGHTS?

You may review, change, or terminate your account at any time. Depending on your region, you may have additional rights under applicable privacy laws.

---

## 9. CONTROLS FOR DO-NOT-TRACK FEATURES

Most web browsers and some mobile operating systems include a Do-Not-Track (“DNT”) feature. We do not currently respond to DNT signals.

---

## 10. DO WE MAKE UPDATES TO THIS NOTICE?

Yes, we will update this privacy notice as necessary to stay compliant with relevant laws.

---

## 11. HOW CAN YOU CONTACT US ABOUT THIS NOTICE?

If you have questions or comments, you may contact us at:

Email: spottrapp@gmail.com  
Website: https://spottr.co.in
